<ul>
<li><a href="http://www.spunk.org/library/consensu/" class="external text" title="http://www.spunk.org/library/consensu/" rel="nofollow">Consensus decision-making</a> at the <a href="/wiki/Spunk_Library" title="Spunk Library">Spunk Library</a></li>
<li><a href="http://seedsforchange.org.uk/free/consens" class="external text" title="http://seedsforchange.org.uk/free/consens" rel="nofollow">"Consensus Decision Making"</a> -- Seeds for Change</li>
<li><a href="http://www.ic.org/pnp/ocac/" class="external text" title="http://www.ic.org/pnp/ocac/" rel="nofollow">"On Conflict and Consensus.</a>" -- C. T. Lawrence Butler and Amy Rothstein (1987) Food Not Bombs Publishing. Also available in <a href="http://www.wandreilagh.org/consensus.pdf" class="external text" title="http://www.wandreilagh.org/consensus.pdf" rel="nofollow">.pdf format</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.consensus.net/" class="external text" title="http://www.consensus.net/" rel="nofollow">"The Formal Consensus Website"</a> -- Based on work by C. T. Lawrence Butler and Amy Rothstein</li>
<li><a href="http://nat.uca.org.au/regulations/2001/pdf/manual_for_meetings.pdf" class="external text" title="http://nat.uca.org.au/regulations/2001/pdf/manual_for_meetings.pdf" rel="nofollow">"A Manual for Meetings, Revised Edition"</a> -- The Uniting Church in Australia</li>
<li><a href="http://www.vernalproject.org/papers/Process.html" class="external text" title="http://www.vernalproject.org/papers/Process.html" rel="nofollow">"Papers on Cooperative Decision-Making"</a> -- Randy Schutt</li>
<li><a href="http://www.diemer.ca/Docs/Diemer-OneVoteforDemocracy.htm" class="external text" title="http://www.diemer.ca/Docs/Diemer-OneVoteforDemocracy.htm" rel="nofollow">"One Vote for Democracy"</a> -- Ulli Diemer</li>
<li><a href="http://www.earlham.edu/~consense/mats.htm" class="external text" title="http://www.earlham.edu/~consense/mats.htm" rel="nofollow">"Some Materials on Consensus."</a> Quaker Foundations of Leadership, 1999. Richmond, Indiana: Earlham College.</li>
</ul>


